ANXIETY THROUGH THE ONGOING STUDY OF OTHER GABA AGONIST MOLECULES. THE TIMING

FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF THESE OTHER MOLECULES IS NOT CERTAIN.

IN APRIL 2003, THE COMPANY ANNOUNCED THAT IT WAS DISCONTINUING DEVELOPMENT

OF ITS LEAD PHOSPHODIESTERASE-4 (PDE-4) INHIBITOR COMPOUND IN PHASE II CLINICAL

TRIALS FOR THE TREATMENT OF ASTHMA AND CHRONIC OBSTRUCTIVE PULMONARY DISEASE

